  "type": "Exercises",
  "number": "3.6",
  "title": "Exercises",
  "body": " Exercises   Analyzing Consonant Features   For each of the following English consonants, identify the place of articulation, manner of articulation, and voicing:   [p]  [ʃ]  [m]  [z]  [tʃ]     Consider: Where in your mouth do you articulate the sound? How is airflow modified? Do your vocal folds vibrate?     Plotting Vowels in the Vowel Space   Using the vowel trapezoid, plot the approximate tongue position for the following vowels and identify their height, backness, and rounding:   [i]  [ɑ]  [u]  [ə]  [ɔ]      Tone vs. Intonation   Explain the difference between tone (as found in tonal languages like Mandarin Chinese) and intonation (as used in English). Give examples from each type of language.     IPA Transcription Practice   Transcribe the following English words in narrow IPA, paying attention to aspiration, vowel quality, and any other phonetic details:   pit  spit  cat  bat  think     Remember: voiceless stops at the beginning of stressed syllables are aspirated in English ([pʰ], [tʰ], [kʰ]), but they're not aspirated after [s].    "
